President Trump welcomed a group of extraordinary teachers to the White House, congratulating the Council of Chief State School Officers on their 65th year recognizing America's outstanding teachers. He also honored Sydney Chaffee, the 2017 National Teacher of the Year, who is a ninth grade humanities teacher at Codman Academy Charter School in Massachusetts. Melania Trump's birthday was also celebrated during the event. The President mentioned that the Oval Office has made some of the biggest executives in the world cry when they visit. He thanked the teachers for their dedication and encouraged them to continue inspiring and teaching their students.